## How Long Does SEO Take for Surrey Businesses?

Timelines vary by competition level and starting point. [How long SEO takes](/blog/how-long-does-seo-take) depends heavily on your market and technical baseline.

**Months 1–3** focus on technical foundations and quick wins — fixing indexation issues, resolving crawlability gaps, implementing structured data correctly, and addressing any Google penalty or manual action history.

**Months 3–6** deliver initial ranking improvements as content with proper topical authority begins indexing. Most clients see meaningful traffic increases in this window for mid-competition queries.

**Months 6–12** produce compound growth as topical authority builds across the topic clusters most relevant to your Surrey market. Competitive local professional services and e-commerce queries begin yielding page-one positions.

## How Much Does an SEO Consultant in Surrey Cost?

**Technical SEO audits** — from £500 for focused audits to £1,200 for comprehensive site health reviews covering crawlability, indexation, Core Web Vitals, and schema implementation.

**Topical maps** — from £800 to £2,500+ depending on industry complexity and the breadth of content clusters required to establish authority in your market.

**Monthly retainers** — from £1,500 for focused SEO strategy and oversight. Compared to a Surrey SEO agency, independent consultant pricing typically delivers the same senior-level quality at 40–60% of the cost. Initial consultations are free.

